# Cursor IDE Rules for Rails Base Template

## Project Context
- Rails 8.1.1 with Ruby 3.2.2
- PostgreSQL database
- Hotwire (Turbo + Stimulus) frontend
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- RSpec for testing
- Devise + Pundit for auth

## Code Style
- Follow Rails conventions
- Use Rails Omakase style (RuboCop enforced)
- Write tests for all new features
- Keep controllers thin, models focused
- Use descriptive names for variables and methods

## File Naming
- snake_case for Ruby files
- kebab-case for JavaScript files
- Models: singular (user.rb)
- Controllers: plural (users_controller.rb)
- Tests: match source file with _spec suffix

## Testing
- Write RSpec tests for all features
- Use Factory Bot for test data
- Test behavior, not implementation
- Aim for >90% coverage

## Git Workflow
- Feature branches for new work
- Descriptive commit messages
- Pre-commit hooks run automatically
- Ensure tests pass before pushing

## Common Commands
- bin/setup: Initial setup
- bin/dev: Start all services
- bin/rspec: Run tests
- bin/rubocop: Lint code
- bin/rails console: Interactive console
